Honeypot-PHP README
===================



Usage:

  # API key from projecthonepot.org
  $api_key = 'asdf1234asdf';

  # ip (ex $_SERVER['REMOTE_ADDR'])
  $addr = '127.1.10.1';

  # create new honeypot instance
  $honeypot = new Honeypot($api_key);  

  # check ip
  if ($honeypot->is_ok($addr)) {
    echo 'address is okay';
  } else {
    echo 'address is NOT OKAY';
  }

If you need more details, you can use the check() method instead:

  $result = $honeypot->check($addr);
  if ($result) {
    if ($result['age'] < 128) {
      if ($result['threat'] > 128) {
        echo 'address is NOT OKAY';
      } else {
        echo 'address is okay (threat too low)';
      }
    } else {
      echo 'address is okay (entry too old)';
    }
  } else {
    echo 'address is okay (not in honeypot database)';
  }
